RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLYING PHANTOM ran with a gain in pace throughout then too the lead late stretch to win the race. I AM THE JUAN ran with early speed then fell back to eighth and then with an even pace then took to the outside like a rocket and down the stretch for place. ATTILAS TORNADO took the early lead then led the pack until about the eighth pole where they hung slightly. RARE COIN ran with an even pace throughout on the outside. ARBITRO started off at the front of the pack as the race progressed they fell back slightly. SUERTUDA ran with a steady pace throughout the race. STORMIN TEXASON ran at the back of the pack then coming down the stretch passed a tired foe then late stretch passed another tired foe. SPICEY SECRET ran at the front of the pack then at the quarter pole they started to fade but not entirely. SMOOTH WATERS had good speed at the start of the race then at the start of the turn faded hard then eased on the stretch. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: ALBUQUERQUE RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 93. Claiming Purse 16600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since July 28 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since April 28 Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. New Mexico Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NORTHERN QUEST ran at the back of the pack then approaching the second turn they started to make a bid for the lead then as they moved thru the pack on the stretch with a strong drive they got the nod at the wire. NORTHCUT set the from right out of the gate and into the first turn, maintained a strong pace and as they came out of the turn he started to draw off from the foes but unfortunately got caught at the wire and missed the nod for the win. MAD LUTHER ran off pace but pressed the pace of the leader throughout the race was never far back until late into the stretch. GOPHER GOLD ran with an even pace throughout the race in the middle of the pack. LUCK IN MY EYES ran with a steady pace in the middle of the pack did not make a move to advance in the positions. IZA DADDY ran at the back of the pack then had a late rally on the stretch to pass some foes. ELLIOT ran at the back of the pack then coming down the main stretch passed some tired foes. TRICKY LEE maintained a moderate pace throughout the race at the back of the pack. LOOKING FOR BULL ran in the middle of the pack then faded hard on the second turn. BRICKHOUSE ran by the front of the pack then coming up the the second turn started to fade back then really faded when they got to the stretch. THIS RACE WAS HAND TIMED.

ENTRY.COMMENT: got the nod, bid on 2nd turn
